bio: 5th President of Kenya, elected in 2022.
Former Deputy President of Kenya, served from 2022 until impeachment in October 2024.
Deputy President of Kenya since October 2024, following the impeachment of Rigathi Gachagua. Former Cabinet Secretary for Interior.

career_history.role: Cabinet Secretary for Interior and National Administration

bio: Former Prime Minister of Kenya (2008-2013) and longtime opposition leader. Ran for president five times. Served as AU Commission Chairperson candidate. Died on October 15, 2025 in India at age 80.
NARC Kenya party leader. Served as Raila Odinga's running mate in the 2022 presidential election. Former Minister for Justice.

career_history.role: Minister for Justice and Constitutional Affairs

bio: Prime Cabinet Secretary of Kenya and ANC party leader. Former Vice President of Kenya.
Speaker of the National Assembly of Kenya. FORD-Kenya party leader and former Minister for Foreign Affairs.
Speaker of the Senate of Kenya. Founder of the Pamoja African Alliance (PAA) party and former Governor of Kilifi County.
4th President of Kenya, serving two terms from 2013 to 2022. Son of founding President Jomo Kenyatta.

career_history.role: Deputy Prime Minister and Minister for Finance

bio: Wiper Democratic Movement party leader and former Vice President of Kenya.
